The paper deals with the synchronization of video streams from rolling shutter cameras, which is a problem commonly encountered in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) applications. The method proposed in the paper involves exploiting the properties of the rolling shutter sensor, which is a topic related to graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of flashes or abrupt lighting changes, which is a technique commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) for synchronization purposes. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.MM, followed by cs.GR, cs.RO, and cs.IT.
